text: Syvert Tobiassen Messel (22 July 1897 - 3 July 1978) was a Norwegian politician for the Liberal Party. He was elected to the Norwegian Parliament from Vest-Agder in 1950, but was not re-elected in 1954. Messel was born in Oddernes and was involved in local politics in Oddernes and its successor municipality Kristiansand, as well as Vest-Agder county council. He was deputy mayor of Oddernes from 1934 to 1945 and mayor from 1945 to 1964. ==References== * Category:1897 births Category:1978 deaths Category:Liberal Party (Norway) politicians Category:Members of the Storting Category:20th-century Norwegian politicians
